# hi-agent — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env` and edit. The binary auto-loads `.env` at startup (via
# `dotenvy`), but existing process env takes precedence — so production
# deployments injecting env via systemd / k8s / compose are unaffected.
# Everything below is optional — the agent runs with all of these unset.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Core
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Model credentials AND the agent behaviour tunables now live in the config store
# (<data_dir>/config.db), set via Settings — not env. That covers the LLM
# key/base/model, every vendor's key/base/model, and the cognition tunables
# (effort, permission mode, pulse interval, reflection cadence, compact ceiling,
# vendor-down thresholds). So there are no AI_API_KEY / HI_AGENT_MODEL /
# HI_AGENT_EFFORT / HI_AGENT_PULSE / VOLCENGINE_* / DOUBAO_* env vars. A fresh
# install works out of the box in the default "xiaoyuanzhu" mode (a broker account
# is auto-created and mints the keys); Settings exposes the common knobs, and the
# deep tunables are editable directly in config.db (sqlite3) if ever needed.

# Dev-only runtime override (point at an external node/adapter/claude to skip
# the first-run download — e.g. when developing offline). All three are
# required together. Debug use only.
# HI_AGENT_DEV_NODE=
# HI_AGENT_DEV_ADAPTER=
# HI_AGENT_DEV_CLAUDE=

# Override the runtime install cache dir (default: OS cache dir). On first run
# the pinned Node + ACP adapter + claude CLI are downloaded/installed here.
# HI_AGENT_RUNTIME_DIR=

# Logging filter — standard tracing-subscriber syntax.
# RUST_LOG=info

# MCP hub socket and shim binary. Override for split-binary / Docker layouts.
# HI_AGENT_MCP_SOCK=./data/mcp.sock
# HI_AGENT_SHIM_BIN=/path/to/hi-agent

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Authentication — gate the web app behind a login (optional; off by default)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# When HI_AGENT_AUTH=on, the browser-facing web app (the SPA + its human API
# channels) requires a logged-in session. hi-agent is a plain OpenID Connect
# relying party — it delegates the login to an external IdP and never touches
# the IdP's social providers. In the intended deployment that IdP is the
# Authentik at account.xiaoyuanzhu.com, whose login screen offers "scan a WeChat QR"
# (Authentik owns the WeChat OAuth source and auto-creates the account on first
# scan). hi-agent just runs the authorization-code flow and sets an encrypted
# session cookie.
#
# Server-to-server callers are NOT gated: the MCP endpoint (/mcp), the phone-
# upload carrier (/api/handoff, /up/*, /api/up/*, /api/qr) and the sense stubs
# stay public. A shared bearer (HI_AGENT_SERVICE_TOKEN, below) additionally
# bypasses the gate on any route, for Feishu / curl journey-tests.
#
# All four OIDC values are REQUIRED when HI_AGENT_AUTH=on (a missing one is a
# hard startup error — fail closed). The redirect URL must be registered on the
# Authentik provider; use the dev one (:5173) when running `make dev`.
# HI_AGENT_AUTH=on
# HI_AGENT_OIDC_ISSUER=https://account.xiaoyuanzhu.com/application/o/hi-agent/
# HI_AGENT_OIDC_CLIENT_ID=
# HI_AGENT_OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=
# HI_AGENT_OIDC_REDIRECT_URL=https://hi.xiaoyuanzhu.com/auth/callback
#   dev: HI_AGENT_OIDC_REDIRECT_URL=https://localhost:5173/auth/callback
#
# Owner-gate: hi-agent is single-tenant (one data dir = one agent), so a valid
# login must also be an OWNER. Set a comma-separated allowlist of identities
# (matched against the token's sub / preferred_username / email). If unset,
# trust-on-first-use binds the first identity to log in (recorded in
# <data_dir>/auth/owner.json) and rejects everyone else.
# HI_AGENT_OWNERS=you@example.com,teammate@example.com
#
# Optional shared bearer that bypasses the browser login on any route (machine
# callers, journey-tests): send `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.
# HI_AGENT_SERVICE_TOKEN=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Speech / Vision / Imagery vendors (STT, TTS, vision, image-gen, video-gen)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# These are configured in the config store (Settings → per-vendor key, base URL,
# model), NOT via env. In the default "xiaoyuanzhu" mode the broker supplies them;
# in BYOK mode you enter your own key in Settings. A vendor with no key is simply
# off (its endpoint returns 501). There are no STT_PROVIDER / TTS_PROVIDER /
# VISION_PROVIDER / IMAGE_GEN_PROVIDER / VIDEO_GEN_PROVIDER / VOLCENGINE_* /
# DOUBAO_* env vars anymore.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Recognition — faces & voices (built-in, local; no API, no provider switch)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Unlike everything above, these are not cloud services with options — each is a
# single local ONNX model with nothing to choose. So there is no provider knob:
# the capability turns on when its model files are present and stays off (never a
# startup failure) when they aren't. Point at the files and it just works.
#
# What it does: recognition is soft evidence the agent weighs, never a verdict.
# Faces in posted stills and in the camera stream get a ⟨faces: …⟩ note; posted
# clips and live-mic speaker turns get a ⟨voice: …⟩ note. Unknown people are
# clustered ("先认人，后命名") under memory/facets/people/<id> at reflection time;
# the agent names an id from conversation (name_person) and fixes mistakes
# (merge_people). Identity = biometric cluster, decided by the agent.
#
# Face — InsightFace buffalo_l (SCRFD detector + ArcFace recognizer). Both files
# required to enable. Camera-stream faces additionally need `ffmpeg` on PATH
# (one keyframe per minute is decoded out); override the binary with FFMPEG_BIN.
# SCRFD_MODEL=./models/det_10g.onnx
# ARCFACE_MODEL=./models/w600k_r50.onnx

# Voice — CAM++ speaker embedding. The one file enables voiceprint.
# CAMPLUS_MODEL=./models/campplus.onnx

# Override the ffmpeg binary used for camera-stream keyframes (default: PATH).
# FFMPEG_BIN=/usr/bin/ffmpeg
